
                                              PRIMITIVES
Type                 Keyword                        Description                             Examples       
                                                    
Integer     -->      int(short, long)               Positive or Negative whole numbers      ex 7, -3
Double      -->      double(float)                  Positive or Negative real numbers       ex 3.19, -2.0
character   -->      char                           A single letter                         ex 'c'. 'F', '2'
True/False  -->      boolean                        True or False                           ex True, False
String      -->      string                         words or sentences                      ex "Hello"


OBJECTS: City, Thing, Robot, etc...
OBJECTS ARE BUILT FROM PRIMITIVE VARIABLES


                                                    EXAMPLES
1. Start with lower case letter
2. name that explains its function
3. Always give value to variables

int yearBorn = 2001; 